1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,400
Planets don't orbit in perfect circles — they dance in ellipses.

2
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:09,200
In the early 1600s, Johannes Kepler cracked the code of planetary movement.

3
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:13,600
He discovered that planets sweep out equal areas in equal times.

4
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:17,200
Imagine a line from the sun to a planet.

5
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:22,800
It covers the same area in a given time, whether it’s close or far.

6
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:30,000
This means planets move faster when they're nearer to the sun — gravity really is a game changer!

7
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,000
Curious about more cosmic mysteries?

8
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Like and follow for more!
